          <td width="83%" class="lighttable">
            <br><P CLASS="post">
              Hey, this is Smurf from Realmud...  and I think there IS a balance.  All of you are forgetting to take into account that being a seraph is a reward.  After a very long, and hard quest(at least for good seraphs) you got your wings and lost ALL your levels.  Of course, if a level 130 is reduced to a level 1, loses all spells, and cannot use most of what they had... its only fair to let them be able to reach their original level quickly, and more interestingly(new places).  I mean, I'm almost finished with the seraph quest, and when I am, I will have almost ALL of the spells in the game.  To do so requires a lot of hard work!!!  When I do get reborn, I will lose ALL those spells, and ALL the money I used to get them.  Warriors, on the other hand get to keep their weapons, or sell them to get their money back.  And you think mage seraphs have it that easy?  I know they can level faster, but they should be able to level faster than a human.  And as I heard someone on another message board say.... seraphs are more of the magical, sophisticated type, and less of the smash/bash/crush type(no offense to warriors).  To get all the items to become a seraph(again, I only know this is true for good quest), You HAVE to be a relatively high level, and you deserve a break.  What is a better reward than giving you wings, and a whole new part of each island to explore and conquer.  You have to admit, Vircom really came through for us with this last patch.  If you think your warrior seraph is not leveling fast enough, then get a few spells, adapt.  Sure, it may be more "honorable" to be a high level w/o being a seraph, but even a level 130 mortal won't stand a chance against Makrsh P'tangh, from what I hear.  Well, this has been the ramblings of a disgruntled Smurf who almost has enough Red Spellbooks :).<br><br>---------------------------------------------------------------------<br>There are very few personal problems that cannot be solved through a suitable application of high explosives.  נננ
